summary: Eid al-Fitr, a significant Muslim holiday marking the end of Ramadan, was widely celebrated around the world. name: National Siblings Day
summary: Today is National Siblings Day! This day is dedicated to celebrating the special bond between brothers and sisters. The day was founded in 1997 by Claudia Evart, who wanted to create a day to honor the relationship between siblings. Evart's own brother had passed away, and she wanted to find a way to keep his memory alive. National Siblings Day is now celebrated every year on April 10th. Many people choose to celebrate this day by spending time with their siblings, sharing memories, and expressing their love and appreciation for each other.

Radio stations and media outlets, including Hot 97 and SiriusXM, paid homage to his legacy with special shows and tributes. Mister Cee's contributions to the New York City hip-hop scene will forever be remembered and celebrated, leaving a void in the hearts of music lovers worldwide.

name: Tara VanDerveer
summary: Legendary women's college basketball coach Tara VanDerveer has announced her retirement after 38 seasons at Stanford University. VanDerveer is the all-time winningest coach in NCAA women's basketball history, accumulating over 1,200 victories during her illustrious career. Under her leadership, Stanford won three national championships and made 28 NCAA Tournament appearances, including 14 Final Four berths. VanDerveer's impact on the sport extends beyond her own team, as she has also served as the head coach of the United States women's national basketball team and has been inducted into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame. Her retirement marks the end of an era for college basketball and leaves a lasting legacy on the sport.

summary: Former NBA star Nate Robinson has revealed that he urgently needs a kidney transplant and fears for his life if he doesn't receive one soon. Robinson, who played for several teams including the New York Knicks, has been diagnosed with kidney failure and has been told he may not have long to live without a transplant. The news has come as a shock to the basketball community and fans, as Robinson was known for his athleticism and vibrant personality during his playing days. Robinson has shared his condition with the public in the hopes of raising awareness about kidney disease and encouraging people to consider organ donation.

name: FISA
summary: Amidst growing concerns, President Trump has called for the elimination of the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act (FISA). House Republicans are facing a contentious debate over reauthorizing FISA, with some seeking compromises while others oppose the warrantless surveillance it allows. Notably, an effort to reauthorize FISA failed in the House due to a conservative revolt. Despite the defeat, some argue that FISA Section 702 should be reauthorized without the warrant requirement. This has prompted a compromise that would maintain the Section 702 authority but implement new oversight measures. However, even with these efforts, it remains uncertain whether a compromise bill will pass.
